==Translingual==

===Symbol===
'''β'''
# The [[lower case]] letter [[beta]], the second letter of the modern [[Greek alphabet]].
# [[beta particle|β-particle]]: [[subatomic particle]].
# Used in [[chemical]] [[nomenclature]].

'''β''''
# The number two in [[Greek numeral]]s.

''',β'''
# The number 2000 in Greek numerals.

===Etymology===
* Derived from the [[Phoenician]] letter [[beth]] [[Image:phoenician_beth.png|20px|Beth]].

===Pronunciation===
* In modern Greek it represents the [[w:Voiced labiodental fricative|voiced labiodental fricative]] sound of '''v''' found in the English words ''have'' and ''vase''.

